---
label: WORKHORSE
summary:
  Shared test fixtures for drag-related tests. Provides a neutral
  `defaultDragInfo`, builder helpers (`boardStackDragAt`,
  `handCardDragAt`), and small utilities (`at`, `stackAt`,
  `defaultBoardRect`, `withWings`). Centralizes DragInfo
  construction so field additions ripple through one module
  instead of every test.
invariants:
  - `boardStackDragAt` → pathFrame = BoardFrame; floaterTopLeft
    interpreted as BOARD frame.
  - `handCardDragAt` → pathFrame = ViewportFrame; floaterTopLeft
    interpreted as VIEWPORT frame; boardRect populated so hit
    tests can translate into board frame.
  - `defaultDragInfo` is neutral-but-valid — a placeholder 2-card
    source at origin, no wings, no hovered wing, no click intent.
    Tests override only what they need via record update.
---

Test fixture module. All drag-related tests should use the builders
here instead of constructing DragInfo records by hand.

Added 2026-04-24 alongside the floaterTopLeft refactor — DragInfo
has 10 fields, and direct construction in every test was a
fragility tax every time the record shape changed.

If a new field lands on DragInfo:
1. Add it to `defaultDragInfo` with a sensible neutral value.
2. Existing tests keep compiling; they get the neutral value.
3. Tests that care override it via `{ drag | newField = ... }`.

See `claude-steve/drag_test_strategy.md` for the broader testing
principles this module serves.
